## Output Format
You MUST output ONLY a valid JSON array of objects. Do not include any explanation before or after the JSON. The JSON format MUST be exactly as follows:

[
  {
    "title": "Short descriptive title of the hypothesis",
    "content": "Detailed explanation of how this root cause occurred, referring to specific technical mechanisms, equipment parameters, or personnel factors.",
    "confidence_score": 0.85,
    "citations": [
      {
        "text": "Exact text quoted directly from one of the evidence chunks above supporting this claim",
        "source": "Name of the source file from the chunk"
      }
    ]
  }
]

## Grounding Rules
- Every hypothesis MUST be backed by at least one direct quote in the "citations" field.
- The "text" in the citation MUST match text present inside the evidence chunks.
- If the evidence is insufficient to generate {{ num_hypotheses }} valid hypotheses, only generate the ones that are supported by the evidence.
- Assign a "confidence_score" between 0.0 and 1.0 based on how strongly the evidence supports the hypothesis.
